Movie: To Live and Die in L.A.
Review: OKAY SO! This feels like a kettle that’s just boiling and boiling and boiling. Rips and roars from start to finish. I wish that killing Chance took maybe, a minute more of screen time. I’d also love to watch this not at 240p.
Re: Burns-Stuart showdown & finale - some questions:
First half of this hooks you so hard but the Faye Dunaway romance is goofy as hell.

Fascinating!!! I had to stop watching at the midpoint to go watch Anyone But You, and I found myself thinking about The Servant the whole time. Love it when a shot sweeps from one position to the next, giving you more information as it goes. It never feels like the camera’s moving just so it can move.
Ok well I had fun? This is fun.

Would love to watch this in one go, ‘twas an interrupted viewing. This didn’t hit me like a train like The French Dispatch did, but I enjoyed it. Especially the Satyajit Ray reference, Wes you sonuva bitch. Personally I think I could’ve played that alien just as well.
